edu.kit.cm.kitcampusguide.standardtypes
Class Route

java.lang.Object
  edu.kit.cm.kitcampusguide.standardtypes.Route
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Route
extends Object
implements Serializable

Represents a route. A route is a list of map positions defining a route by going from one of them to the next. The bounding box is a section of the map so that all waypoints of the route lie within. Stores the waypoints defining the route and a bounding box.

Author:
fred

Method Detail

getStart

public MapPosition getStart()
Returns the MapPosition at which the route begins. Should be identical to getWaypoints.get(0). Used to display the route-from marker.

Returns:
The MapPosition at which the route begins.

getEnd

public MapPosition getEnd()
Returns the MapPosition at which the route ends. Should be identical to getWaypoints.get(getWaypoints.getSize()-1). Used to display the route-to marker.

Returns:
The MapPosition at which the route ends.

getWaypoints

public List<MapPosition> getWaypoints()
Returns a list of MapPositions defining the route. This list starts at the beginning of the route and ends at the last. To draw the route, simply draw a route between all adjacent map positions.

Returns:
A list of MapPositions defining the route.

getBoundingBox

public MapSection getBoundingBox()
Returns the bounding box of the route. It is the map section where the whole route lies in. To be used to get the section to be shown after the route has been calculated.

Returns:
The bounding box of the route.
